  <h2>What AC repair costs in Tampa (and what drives the price)</h2>
  <p>Honest answer: most Tampa AC repairs land between <strong>$150 and $600</strong>, with a capacitor or thermostat at the low end and a compressor or evaporator coil at the high end. Rather than quote a fake flat number online, here is what actually moves your price up or down:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>The failed part.</strong> A $20 capacitor versus a sealed-system refrigerant leak are very different repairs.</li>
    <li><strong>Refrigerant type.</strong> Older R-410A and the newer R-32 / R-454B systems carry different refrigerant costs per pound.</li>
    <li><strong>Access.</strong> An attic air handler in 140° Florida heat takes longer than a garage unit at eye level.</li>
    <li><strong>Whether maintenance was kept up.</strong> A neglected coil or drain line turns a simple visit into a bigger one. A <a href="/services/ac-maintenance-tampa/">maintenance plan</a> keeps most of these from happening, and our guide on <a href="/blogs/regular-ac-maintenance-prevents-costly-repairs/">how maintenance prevents costly repairs</a> shows why.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Whatever the repair, you get a <strong>written flat-rate quote before we touch a tool</strong>, the diagnostic fee is waived when you move forward with us, and if the number is bigger than you expected, we offer <a href="/financing/">0% financing</a> so a hot house never has to wait on a paycheck.</p>

  <OwnerTip>
    <p>"The cheapest repair is the one you never need. Most of the no-cool calls we run in July could have been prevented by a 45-minute spring tune-up. If your system is over six years old and has not been serviced this year, book a <a href="/services/ac-maintenance-tampa/">maintenance visit</a> before the next heat wave - it is the best money you can spend on your AC."</p>
  </OwnerTip>

  <h2>What our AC repair visit actually looks like</h2>
  <p>Every I Care Air Care repair call follows the same structure because transparency is the fastest way to earn repeat customers:</p>
  <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 space-y-2 text-slate-700 mt-4">
    <li><strong>Arrival window confirmed by text.</strong> You know exactly when the tech is coming - not a 4-hour window.</li>
    <li><strong>Full system diagnostic.</strong> We check refrigerant pressures, superheat/subcool, capacitor microfarads, contactor pitting, blower amps, temp-split across the coil, and thermostat signal. We take photos of anything relevant.</li>
    <li><strong>Flat-rate written quote.</strong> You see the price before any repair begins. No per-hour surprises.</li>
    <li><strong>The repair.</strong> OEM or manufacturer-approved parts whenever possible.</li>
    <li><strong>Verification & cleanup.</strong> We confirm the system is running within spec, clean up, and email you a full service report.</li>
  </ol>

