  <h2>When AC repair is the right call (and when it isn't)</h2>
  <p>We never push replacement on a repair call. If your system is under 10 years old, has a working compressor, and the repair cost is less than about 30% of a comparable new install, repairing is usually the better economic move. Once you're past 12 years with an R-22 system or a failing compressor, the math flips hard toward <a href="/services/ac-replacement-tampa/">AC replacement</a> or a <a href="/services/hvac-installation-tampa/">high-efficiency new install</a> - especially with 2026 refrigerant regulations phasing out older equipment. If efficiency is the goal, our <a href="/blogs/seer2-explained-florida-2026/">SEER2 guide for Florida</a> breaks down what the new ratings actually save you.</p>

  <p>If replacement is the right call, we'll tell you, show you the numbers, and lay out the options side by side. Either way, you decide with real math, not a sales pitch.</p>

